def plot_dist(col, ax):
    if col not in ['age', 'balance', 'day','duration','campaign', 'previous']:
        train[col].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', facecolor='y', ax=ax)
    else:
        train[col].plot(kind='density', ax=ax, bw_method = 0.15, color='b', xlim=(train[col].min(), train[col].max()))
    ax.set_title("{} on train".format(col), fontsize= 18)
    return ax

f, ax = plt.subplots(4,4, figsize = (22,15))
f.tight_layout(h_pad=9, w_pad=2, rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.93])
cols = train.columns
k = 0
for i in range(4):
    for j in range(4):
        plot_dist(cols[k], ax[i][j])
        k += 1
__ = plt.suptitle("Initial Distributions of features", fontsize= 25)

def plot_barh(df,col, cmap = None, stacked=False, norm = None):
    df.plot(kind='barh', colormap=cmap, stacked=stacked)
    fig = plt.gcf()
    fig.set_size_inches(24,12)
    plt.title("job vs {}-feedback -  train {}".format(col, '(Normalized)' if norm else ''), fontsize= 20)
    plt.ylabel('job', fontsize = 18)
    plot = plt.xlabel('Frequency', fontsize=18)
    
def norm_counts(t):
    norms = np.linalg.norm(t.fillna(0), axis=1)
    t_norm = t[0:0]
    for row, euc in zip(t.iterrows(), norms):
        t_norm.loc[row[0]] = list(map(lambda x: x/euc, list(row[1])))
    return t_norm

import pandas as pd
import os
import glob

path = "C:/Users/haimr/proj/predictions/"
csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path, "*.csv"))

# loop over the list of csv files
for f in csv_files:
    x=f.split("_")[0]
    if (x.split('\\')[-1]) != "train":
        df = pd.read_csv(f)
        y_true = df["class"]
        y_preds = df["prediction"]
        classes = y_true.unique()
        mtx = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_preds, labels=classes, )
        plt.title((f.split("\\")[-1]).split(".")[0])
        ConfusionMatrixDisplay(mtx, display_labels=classes).plot(cmap=plt.cm.Blues)
        fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.40)
